        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix #87407: [Bug]: retry on UND_ERR_SOCKET keep-alive failures",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: Undici keep-alive pooled sockets can fail with `UND_ERR_SOCKET` on first use after being idle. This causes model requests to fail without retry, cascading through fallback models (#87407).\n- Solution: add `isUndiciSocketError()` detector and one-retry logic in `buildGuardedModelFetch`. On `UND_ERR_SOCKET`, the fetch is retried once with a fresh TCP connection. The local service lease is properly released on retry failure.\n- What changed: `provider-transport-fetch.ts` — new `isUndiciSocketError()` helper + retry in catch block. `provider-transport-fetch.test.ts` — 5 new tests.\n- What did NOT change: no API, config, schema, or non-undici behavior changes. Only one retry attempt to avoid infinite loops.\n\n## Maintainer checklist\n- Fix classification: Root-cause bug fix in provider transport fetch\n- Maintainer-ready confidence: High — 83/83 tests pass including 5 new tests\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n**Behavior or issue addressed:**\nUndici keep-alive socket reuse failures (UND_ERR_SOCKET) cause model requests to fail without retry, cascading through fallback models.\n\n**Real environment tested:**\n- Platform: Linux x86_64\n- Node.js: v22.22.0\n- Runtime: Vitest v4.1.8\n- Branch: fix/anthropic-undo-socket-87407 (01d31cec0)\n\n**Exact steps or command run after the patch:**\n```\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/provider-transport-fetch.test.ts --reporter=verbose\n```\n\n**After-fix evidence:**\n```\n Test Files  1 passed (1)\n      Tests  83 passed (83)\n```\n\n**Observed result after fix:**\n- `isUndiciSocketError` correctly detects direct and nested UND_ERR_SOCKET errors ✓\n- `isUndiciSocketError` returns false for non-socket, null, and different error codes ✓\n- Existing buildGuardedModelFetch tests continue to pass ✓\n\n**What was not tested:**\n- Live undici connection pool with actual keep-alive timeout (requires network-level simulation)",
